      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "oh okay, so it's the phase shift thing. that makes sense. so basically the reactance is like an extra layer of resistance that acts differently because of the timing? it's kind of hard to visualize how that \"opposition\" actually works in the circuit compared to just a normal resistor.",
      "beast_suffix": "",
